[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now Naomi"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " had a relative"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " on her husband’s side of the family named Boaz. He was a wealthy, prominent man from the clan of Elimelech."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " One day Ruth the Moabite said to Naomi, “Let me go"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to the fields so I can gather"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " grain behind whoever permits me to do so.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Naomi"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " replied, “You may go, my daughter.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Ruth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " went and gathered grain in the fields"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " behind the harvesters. Now she just happened to end up"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the portion of the field belonging to Boaz, who was from the clan of Elimelech."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now at that very moment,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Boaz arrived from Bethlehem"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and greeted"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the harvesters, “May the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " be with you!” They replied,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “May the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " bless you!” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Boaz asked"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his servant"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in charge of the harvesters, “To whom does this young woman belong?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The servant in charge of the harvesters replied, “She’s the young Moabite woman who came back with Naomi from the region of Moab. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " She asked,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ‘May I follow the harvesters and gather"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " grain among the bundles?’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Since she arrived she has been working hard"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " from this morning until now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " – except for"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sitting"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the resting hut"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a short time.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Boaz said to Ruth, “Listen carefully,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my dear!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Do not leave to gather grain in another field. You need not"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " go beyond the limits of this field. You may go along beside"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my female workers."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Take note of"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the field where the men"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " are harvesting and follow behind with the female workers."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I will tell the men"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " to leave you alone."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When you are thirsty, you may go to"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the water jars"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and drink some of the water"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the servants draw.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Ruth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " knelt before him with her forehead to the ground"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and said to him, “Why are you so kind"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and so attentive to me,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " even though"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I am a foreigner?”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Boaz replied to her,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “I have been given a full report of"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " all that you have done for your mother-in-law following the death of your husband – how you left"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your father and your mother, as well as your homeland, and came to live among people you did not know previously."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " May the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " reward your efforts!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " May your acts of kindness be repaid fully"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " God of Israel, from whom you have sought protection!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " She said, “You really are being kind to me,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " sir,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for you have reassured"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and encouraged"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " me, your servant,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " even though I am"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " not one of your servants!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Later during the mealtime Boaz said to her, “Come here and have"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " some food! Dip your bread"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the vinegar!” So she sat down beside the harvesters. Then he handed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " her some roasted grain. She ate until she was full and saved the rest."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When she got up to gather grain, Boaz told"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his male servants, “Let her gather grain even among"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the bundles! Don’t chase her off!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Make sure you pull out"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ears of grain for her and drop them so she can gather them up. Don’t tell her not to!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So she gathered grain in the field until evening. When she threshed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " what she had gathered, it came to about thirty pounds"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of barley!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " She carried it back to town, and her mother-in-law saw"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " how much grain"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " she had gathered. Then Ruth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " gave her the roasted grain she had saved from mealtime."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Her mother-in-law asked her,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “Where did you gather grain today? Where did you work? May the one who took notice of you be rewarded!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Ruth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " told her mother-in-law with whom she had worked. She said, “The name of the man with whom I worked today is Boaz.” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Naomi said to her daughter-in-law, “May he be rewarded by the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " because he"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has shown loyalty to the living on behalf of the dead!”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then Naomi said to her, “This man is a close relative of ours; he is our guardian.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Ruth the Moabite replied, “He even"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " told me, ‘You may go along beside my servants"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " until they have finished gathering all my harvest!’”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Naomi then said to her daughter-in-law Ruth, “It is good, my daughter, that you should go out to work with his female servants."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " That way you will not be harmed, which could happen in another field.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So Ruth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " worked beside"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Boaz’s female servants, gathering grain until the end of the barley harvest as well as the wheat harvest."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " After that she stayed home with her mother-in-law."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]